<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Beware the scam artists!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Kayleigh">Kayleigh</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:55 a.m. 9/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Beware the scam artists!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/karana.cgi?read=38" TARGET=_self>Re: Beware the scam artists!</A> (Sedeth of Karana)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Unfortunatly i read somewhere that 989 has decided that this "thieving business" is within the boundries of the game and there isn't anything that they can or will do about it. I can tell you one way how they do it, a real good cunning artists will do it like this : (i tried it myself on a friend and it works) You will agree to make a trade for a set price, i will put my object (the one you want to buy from me) in the trading window, you think you're clever and check if it's the right item and it will show you that it is. Now you will put 5plat or more in your trading screen and click trade... now this is the part that you have to be aware of, once you clicked trade you canot cancel the trade, so i will go ahead and put a worthless item in my trading screen and you won't even notice it. You just bought a complete worthless item from me for a lot of money !!! There isn't anything you can do except to wait for the trader to click the button before you do. Personally i don't like to live in a world like that where you can't trust anyone, so i just keep my eyes and ears open for names that i hear a lot of tricking people and having a bad name....

<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
